-- Italy Gasoline, Diesel Demand Dropped in December, Ministry Says
-- B y   K o n s t a n t i n   R o z h n o v
-- 2013-01-17T13:14:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-17/italy-gasoline-diesel-demand-dropped-in-december-ministry-says.html
Italy’s gasoline and diesel
consumption fell in December by the most since September from a
year earlier, according to  data  from the Ministry of Economic
Development.  Gasoline use dropped 12 percent to 681,000 metric tons,
data posted today on the ministry’s website show. Diesel demand
plunged about 14 percent to 2.21 million tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Konstantin Rozhnov in London at 
 krozhnov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
